<HEAD>Norwegian Phones Home, Disrupts Plans for His Memorial</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS thruout to CORRECT typo in lede, MINOR EDITING</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORSGRUNN, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 40-year-old musician interrupted the
planning for his own memorial service by calling from Denmark to
ask if he could come home, a newspaper reported.
   Morten Berntsen disappeared six months ago and the evidence
indicated that he jumped to his death from a bridge, the newspaper
Verdens Gang said Friday.
   The jazz musician was unaware that a memorial sevice was being
planned for Friday when he called last weekend and asked a shocked
friend to come get him in Denmark, said the report.
   The paper said Berntsen apparently had been under a lot of
stress due to financial problems and recalled little about the six
months he was gone.
