<HEAD>Victims' Parents Get $1.1 Million in Delta Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Delta Air Lines agreed to pay $1.1
million in damages to the parents of a man killed in the 1985 crash
of a jetliner outside Dallas.
   The award to the parents of Michael Epstein, 24, of West Palm
Beach, was announced Thursday, just an hour before Leo Epstein, 72,
and his former wife, Nancy Epstein, 68, were to go to trial against
Delta.
   Flight 191 crashed on approach to Dallas-Fort Worth
International Airport in a violent thunderstorm Aug. 2, 1985.
   On Wednesday, a six-member federal jury awarded $3.4 million to
the parents of Julie Ann Zarnt, 15, another victim of the crash.
   In all, 182 claims and 115 lawsuits have been filed against
Delta since the crash. Delta Has paid out more than $67 million in
settlements.
