<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     11-18 0505</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0522</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cold Wave Freezes Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Fair and cold weather prevailed across much of the nation early
today, with a cold front extending into the Southeast expected to
take freezing temperatures as far south as Florida.
   Temperatures dipped to the 20s and 30s throughout the East,
Midwest and Northwest, and fell to as low as 6 degrees in
Minneapolis-St. Paul and 13 degrees in Des Moines, Ill. Snow fell
in Sault St. Marie, Mich.
   In parts of the South, temperatures dropped to the 30s early
today. Freezing temperatures were expected in northeast Florida,
Georgia, Alabama, the Carolinas and Virginia.
   Record low temperatures for the date Friday included 8 degrees
at Gilbert, Ark., and 24 degrees at Greer, S.C.
   The cold front and snow moved through Chicago early Friday
evening, causing several accidents during rush hour.
   Two people died in separate accidents in Wisconsin after a snow
storm iced pavements. Milwaukee police reported 120 accidents in a
four-hour period.
   ``It's like driver's education,'' Eau Claire police Sgt. Jerry
Berg said. ``That first snowfall, you have to teach them all how to
drive again.''
   Snow fell Friday evening over southeast Minnesota, northeast
Iowa, eastern Wisconsin, northern Illinois, northern Indiana,
Michigan and northwest New York. Rain dampened parts of Iowa and
Nebraska and the Texas Gulf Coast.
   Not all of the nation was shivering under a cold front.
   Record highs for the date were set in Northern California,
including 80 degrees at Moffett Field Naval Air Station, near
Mountain View, and 75 degrees in Oakland.
   The high temperature for the nation Friday was 88 degrees at
Borrego Springs, Calif.
   Other reports at 3 a.m. EST:
   _East: Atlanta 33 partly cloudy; Boston 34 fair; Charleston,
S.C. 39 fair; Chattanooga 33 fair; Cincinnati 37 snow; Cleveland 32
windy; Detroit 26 partly cloudy; Hatteras 48 fair; Jacksonville 36
fair; Key West 70 windy; Knoxville 35 fair; Macon 34 cloudy; Miami
61 fair; New York 41 fair; Philadelphia 36 fair; Pittsburgh 33
windy; Portland, Maine 29 fair; Richmond 35 partly cloudy; Tampa 47
fair; Washington, D.C. 36 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 12 cloudy; Chicago 20 partly cloudy; Denver
31 fair; Des Moines 13 fair; Indianapolis 26 partly cloudy; Kansas
City 20 fair; Little Rock 40 fair; Louisville 39 cloudy; Memphis 38
partly cloudy; Nashville 38 fair; New Orleans 47 rain; North Platte
17 fair; Oklahoma City 39 fair; Omaha 14 fair; Rapid City 25 partly
cloudy; St. Louis 27 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 6 fair; Sault St.
Marie 18 snow; San Antonio 54 foggy.
   _West: Anchorage 30 fair; Boise 39 foggy; Casper 40 cloudy;
Fairbanks 3 snow; Great Falls 45 windy; Honolulu 73 fair; Las Vegas
53 fair; Los Angeles 60 foggy; Medford 34 fair; Pendleton 39 foggy;
Phoenix 58 fair; Portland, Ore. 43 fair; Reno 37 fair; Salt Lake
City 34 foggy; San Diego 57 foggy; San Francisco 59 fair; Seattle
47 cloudy; Spokane 38 foggy.
   _International: Calgary partly cloudy; Montreal 32 cloudy;
Ottawa 25 partly cloudy; Regina 14 snow; Toronto 25 partly cloudy;
Winnipeg 5 fair.
