<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--SpeedSeized     11-18 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Speed Seized,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Huge Seizure of Methamphetamine in California</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities arrested four men and seized
half a ton of methamphetamine in what state Attorney General John
Van de Kamp said was the biggest seizure of the drug in history.
   At the rate of up to $10,000 a pound, the haul was worth nearly
$100 million, Vam de Kamp said Friday. ``The entire annual budget
of the San Francisco Police Department is $180 million,'' he said.
   The methamphetamine, or ``speed,'' was recovered in October from
a storage locker in Hayward, across the San Francisco Bay, Van de
Kamp said. Sixteen kilograms of cocaine also were seized.
   Methamphetamine, especially a smokeable version called ``ice,''
has grown increasingly popular in recent years on the West Coast.
