<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Philippines-Bus     11-18 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Philippines-Bus,0148</SECOND>
<HEAD>Buses Collide, Plunge Into Ravine, Killing 12</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ILIGAN, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger bus collided with a
minibus Saturday in a southern town, hurtling both vehicles into a
ravine and killing 12 people and wounding 21, officials said.
   Mito Lopez, a spokesman for the Fortune Bus Company, said the
accident took place in the town of Kauswagan in Lanao del Norte
province, about 490 miles southeast of Manila.
   Lopez said the bus was on a sharp curve en route to Iligan from
the adjacent province of Zamboanga del Sur when it hit the minibus
coming from the opposite direction.
   The impact threw both vehicles into a 30-foot-deep ravine, Lopez
said. The dead included two Fortune passengers and the driver, and
nine people in the other vehicle.
   He said records of how many people were on both vehicles were
unavailable.
