<FILEID>AP-NR-11-18-89 1832EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-Israel     11-18 0267</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Israel,0275</SECOND>
<HEAD>Masked Assailants Kill Woman, Troops Wound 11 Palestinians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Masked assailants stabbed and beat to death an
Arab woman Saturday and Israeli troops opened fire on Palestinians
in the occupied territories, wounding at least 11, hospital
officials reported.
   They identified the woman as 40-year-old Atiyat Inajar and said
she died of the wounds at the Nasser Hospital in the
Israeli-occupied Gaza Strip town of Khan Yunis.
   Palestinian reporters in the Gaza Strip said she was suspected
of immoral behavior and of providing assistance to Israeli
authorities. The Israeli military command confirmed the death and
said the killing was under investigation.
   Her death brought to 147 the number of Palestinians slain by
Arabs on suspicion of being pro-Israeli collaborators during the
23-month uprising against Israeli rule in the West Bank and the
Gaza Strip.
   At least 615 Palestinians have been killed by Israeli gunfire in
the revolt, and 42 Israelis have perished in the violence.
   Arab doctors said troops opened fire to disperse stone-throwing
Palestinian youths in the Gaza village of Beit Hanoun and the Shati
refugee camp, wounding eleven protesters aged 16 to 23.
   The army command said it had no information about the incidents.
   Isa Ali Sabah, 29, of El-Khadr village near Bethlehem, died at
East Jerusalem's Mukassed Hospital Saturday after suffering head
injuries when stones were thrown at his car in the West Bank last
month. Israel radio said Sabah lost control of his car during the
assault and it crashed.
   The broadcast quoted Arab residents as blaming Jews for the
attack. Police said they no information about the case.
</TEXT>
