<FILEID>AP-NR-11-18-89 0626EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--MexicanJails     11-18 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Mexican Jails,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>Washington Asks Mexico About Renting Jail Space</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state prison official wants to rent jail cells
in Mexico to lock up illegal aliens who are convicted in Washington
of dealing drugs.
   Joseph Lehman, deputy secretary of corrections, proposed the
idea last month in a letter to Enrique Loaeza, Mexico's consul
general in San Francisco.
   Loaeza forwarded the request to his government, which has not
replied.
   Lehman said illegal aliens from Mexico who are convicted in
Washington of drug dealing and other crimes could be jailed more
cheaply in Mexico.
   Dick Milne, Gov. Booth Gardner's press secretary, said Gardner
knows about Lehman's effort. He called it an ``interesting idea''
but would not comment further.
</TEXT>
