<HEAD>Eight High School Students Charged in Alleged Gang Rape</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORTH MIAMI, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seven high school students have been
arrested and an eighth is being sought for the gang rape of a
19-year-old woman, police said Friday.
   The students at North Miami High School, including seven members
of the football team, allegedly assaulted the woman Aug. 1 at a
North Miami apartment complex.
   All eight students have been charged with sexual battery, police
said.
   The victim, whom police described as a night student at the
school, knew some of the suspects and had agreed to have dinner
with two of them when the assault began, police said.
   ``Sometime during the assault, one individual left, went back to
the school and got the other five or six people,'' said North Miami
Police Det. Don Diescidue.
   Three of the youths appeared Friday in juvenile court before
Judge Thomas Peterson and were ordered detained. Police have
identified the eighth suspect and were seeking him Friday,
Detective Don Diescidue said.
</TEXT>
