<FIRST>r a AM-SmithHospitalized     11-18 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Smith Hospitalized,0169</SECOND>
<HEAD>Margaret Chase Smith Hospitalized in Chicago</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Margaret Chase Smith, Maine's longtime Republican
senator, was in a hospital Friday after complaining of chest pains
a day earlier, according to spokesman who said she got sick after
eating airline food.
   ``They think it was basically due to digestion,'' but the
hospital ran some tests since chest pains can also be an indication
of heart problems, her spokesman and lawyer, Merton G. Henry, said
from his office in Portland, Maine.
   ``She's in fair condition this morning in the intensive care
unit and showing steady improvement,'' said Janice Youngwith, a
spokeswoman at Resurrection Hospital.
   Mrs. Smith, 91, became ill on a flight from Bangor, Maine, to
Chicago en route to a meeting in Indianapolis on Wednesday. Henry
expected her to return to Maine within a few days.
   Mrs. Smith served in the Senate from 1948 until 1972, when she
was defeated in a bid for a fifth term by Democrat William D.
Hathaway.
</TEXT>
