<HEAD>Fixed-Rate Mortgages Dip to 9.72 Percent, Survey Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages are currently
averaging 9.72 percent, according to a national survey released
Friday by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   The rate was down from 9.79 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.49 percent this week, down from 8.52
